arlpy --- ARL Python Tools
Mandar Chitre (Acoustic Research Laboratory, National University of Singapore)
Upstream: https://github.com/org-arl/arlpy

UACPY does not vendor the full arlpy source tree. Instead, a small number
of domain-utility functions have been adapted from arlpy into UACPY's own
modules. The BSD-3-Clause license text for those adapted portions is
reproduced in LICENSE (next to this file).

Files in UACPY containing arlpy-adapted code:

    uacpy/core/acoustics.py
        Functions adapted from arlpy.uwa (BSD-3-Clause, (c) 2016 Mandar Chitre):
          - soundspeed          (Mackenzie 1981)
          - absorption          (Francois-Garrison)
          - absorption_filter
          - density             (Fofonoff IES-80)
          - reflection_coeff
          - doppler
          - bubble_resonance

    uacpy/acoustic_signal/advanced.py
        Functions adapted from arlpy.signal (BSD-3-Clause, (c) 2016 Mandar Chitre):
          - time, nextpow2, pow2, padded_shape (utilities)
          - lfilter0                           (zero-phase filtering)
          - and other signal-processing helpers

All adapted functions preserve their original scientific formulas;
UACPY-side changes are limited to Python-level formatting (type hints,
docstrings, PEP 8 spacing). See the header of each adapted file for
per-file attribution.
